WEBVTT

00:00.968 --> 00:03.171
* Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba *

00:03.204 --> 00:04.672
* Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da
Let's go!

00:04.705 --> 00:06.374
* We'll be there

00:06.407 --> 00:09.043
* A wink and a smile
and a great old time *

00:09.077 --> 00:11.245
* Yeah, we'll be there

00:11.279 --> 00:13.347
* Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found *

00:13.381 --> 00:15.683
* We'll be there
when you turn that corner *

00:15.716 --> 00:17.017
* We'll jump out the bush

00:17.051 --> 00:18.719
* With a big bear hug
and a smile *

00:18.752 --> 00:20.188
* We'll be there

00:24.925 --> 00:27.328
Oo, hoo-hoo!
Another new Boba place!

00:27.361 --> 00:28.729
Let's check it out.

00:28.762 --> 00:30.498
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
hold it, hold it.

00:30.531 --> 00:31.999
Where do you think
you're going?

00:32.032 --> 00:33.701
Uhh...to get Boba?

00:33.734 --> 00:36.670
Nuh-uh -- no naked people
allowed -- new policy.

00:36.704 --> 00:38.072
But we're naked always.

00:38.106 --> 00:40.874
Not my problem.
Get some clothes or get lost.

00:40.908 --> 00:43.077
Aww...

00:43.111 --> 00:45.346
It's okay, Pan Pan,
we'll figure something out.

00:45.379 --> 00:47.448
Hmm. Huh? Aha!

00:47.481 --> 00:48.916
I got an idea.

00:57.325 --> 00:58.426
[ Slurping ]
Ahh!

00:58.459 --> 00:59.860
Good thinking, Grizz.

00:59.893 --> 01:01.595
I guess we can get rid
of these clothes now.

01:01.629 --> 01:03.531
I don't know about you guys,
but I'm keeping mine.

01:03.564 --> 01:04.532
I mean,
this suit is great!

01:04.565 --> 01:06.800
I feel so...important.

01:06.834 --> 01:08.536
Besides,
it fits me perfectly,

01:08.569 --> 01:10.804
and it makes my butt look good
too, you know?

01:10.838 --> 01:12.406
Feels comfortable -- Huh?

01:12.440 --> 01:13.874
Sir, please sit down,

01:13.907 --> 01:16.744
or do you want to get your
whole company late for work?

01:16.777 --> 01:17.845
Huh.

01:19.347 --> 01:21.549
Hey,
a-are you the new guy?

01:21.582 --> 01:25.386
Um, yeah...that's me.
I'm one of you guys!

01:25.419 --> 01:27.955
Grizz, do we --
G-Grizz?

01:27.988 --> 01:28.956
Where did he go?

01:28.989 --> 01:30.158
I thought he was right
behind us.

01:30.191 --> 01:31.259
...and I said "Desert?

01:31.292 --> 01:32.293
I thought you meant
dessert!"

01:32.326 --> 01:34.562
[ Laughter ]

01:34.595 --> 01:37.231
Oh, I guess he made
some new friends.

01:37.265 --> 01:38.899
Oh, well.
[ Slurps ]

01:38.932 --> 01:40.000
Huh.

01:40.033 --> 01:41.635
Huh!

01:41.669 --> 01:44.738
Mm, Mm Mm. Throwing trash
on the ground, eh?

01:44.772 --> 01:47.074
Tsk tsk tsk!
You're under arrest!

01:47.107 --> 01:49.109
No! I was just...I-I
mean...I-I...wasn't...

01:49.143 --> 01:51.579
Ahh, I'm just playin'
with you. [ Giggles ]

01:51.612 --> 01:53.481
Oh.
[ Laughs nervously ]

01:53.514 --> 01:55.015
Oh, I like your cardigan,
by the way.

01:55.048 --> 01:57.185
Actually, I like
your overall style, man.

01:57.218 --> 01:58.152
Really?

01:58.186 --> 01:59.420
I'm Sam, by the way.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.155
Oh. Um, I'm Panda?

02:01.189 --> 02:03.624
Wait, you're a panda,
and your name's "Panda?"

02:03.657 --> 02:04.925
Uh, yeah?

02:04.958 --> 02:07.761
[ Laughs ]
That is so funny!

02:07.795 --> 02:09.830
[ Laughs nervously ]
I guess that is kind of weird.

02:09.863 --> 02:12.633
So, uh, what's up with
the extra seat on your bike?

02:12.666 --> 02:15.369
Uh-huh. Are you asking me
if I have a boyfriend?

02:15.403 --> 02:17.671
Oh, no! I wasn't trying to --
I just mean -- I was just --

02:17.705 --> 02:19.773
Nope, I don't have anyone
to ride this bike with.

02:19.807 --> 02:21.975
Oh. [ Laughs nervously ]
Okay, cool.

02:22.009 --> 02:23.043
Here! Come on!

02:23.076 --> 02:24.912
Oh. Okay.

02:25.846 --> 02:28.782
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

02:28.816 --> 02:30.451
That's awesome.
[ Growls ]

02:30.484 --> 02:31.552
[ Camera Shutter Clicks ]

02:31.585 --> 02:33.120
Sir, sir!
Over here, please!

02:33.153 --> 02:34.622
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
Ice Bear will
destroy paparazzi.

02:34.655 --> 02:36.156
Oh, oh,
uh, excuse me, man.

02:36.190 --> 02:37.958
I'm actually a fashion
photographer,

02:37.991 --> 02:39.527
and I just love
your look --

02:39.560 --> 02:41.362
The simple color scheme,
the composition...

02:41.395 --> 02:43.297
I just love the minimalist style
you're going for.

02:43.331 --> 02:44.465
Thanks, man.

02:44.498 --> 02:45.733
Ice Bear happy to help.

02:45.766 --> 02:47.501
[ Laughs ]
I love the way you talk.

02:47.535 --> 02:48.902
Hey, you got some time?

02:48.936 --> 02:50.738
I have some friends that you
should really meet.

02:50.771 --> 02:53.674
[ Bell jingles,
cheering and laughing ]

02:53.707 --> 02:56.310
Ice Bear is down
to meet some friends.

02:56.344 --> 02:58.045
[ Tires screech ]

02:58.078 --> 02:59.179
[ Air hisses ]

03:01.515 --> 03:02.850
Whoa.

03:02.883 --> 03:05.986
[ Bird squawking ]

03:06.019 --> 03:07.355
[ Ding! ]

03:12.460 --> 03:13.694
We'll have those
T.P.S. Reports

03:13.727 --> 03:15.095
ready for delivery
tomorrow morning.

03:15.128 --> 03:16.864
Well, this was fun,
but I should get going.

03:16.897 --> 03:18.266
Hey, come on, new guy!

03:18.299 --> 03:20.768
Hey, everyone, I want you
to meet the new guy!

03:20.801 --> 03:22.536
New guy. I didn't know there was
a job opening.

03:22.570 --> 03:23.671
What have they
got you doing?

03:23.704 --> 03:26.006
Um...office stuff?

03:26.039 --> 03:28.242
[ Laughter ]

03:28.276 --> 03:29.843
You're funny, newbie!

03:29.877 --> 03:32.112
You're gonna fit
right in here, new guy.

03:32.145 --> 03:32.946
[ Laughs ]

03:35.383 --> 03:36.784
[ Sizzling ]

03:43.391 --> 03:44.725
[ Chair squeaking ]

03:46.627 --> 03:48.262
[ Laughter ]

03:48.296 --> 03:49.697
He's coming!

03:49.730 --> 03:51.198
-Huh? Who? Wha-?
-He's coming!

03:51.231 --> 03:52.366
He's coming!

03:52.400 --> 03:56.036
-He's coming!
-Everyone, get back to work!

03:56.069 --> 03:57.405
[ Ding! ]

03:57.438 --> 03:58.539
[ Keyboard clacking ]

03:58.572 --> 03:59.407
Whew!

03:59.440 --> 04:01.074
Hey, great work!

04:01.108 --> 04:02.543
Fantastic!

04:02.576 --> 04:04.645
Loving it, just great.

04:04.678 --> 04:06.747
-Hello, sir.
-Hello, employee!

04:06.780 --> 04:08.549
[ Gasps ] The boss!

04:08.582 --> 04:09.817
[ Groans ]

04:09.850 --> 04:11.285
Uh, hey friend, um,
mind scooting a bit?

04:11.319 --> 04:13.186
No! Get away!

04:15.088 --> 04:17.391
I thought I told you fellas
to stop groveling at my feet.

04:17.425 --> 04:20.661
[ Laughs ] You must be new.
What's your name, son?

04:20.694 --> 04:21.895
Um, Grizz.

04:21.929 --> 04:24.398
Grizz, huh?
Let me guess, first day?

04:24.432 --> 04:25.232
[ Nervously ] Yep.

04:25.265 --> 04:26.634
Casual. I like it!

04:26.667 --> 04:28.101
How are you
enjoying it here?

04:28.135 --> 04:30.304
What can this company do
to be better?

04:30.338 --> 04:31.939
Um...

04:31.972 --> 04:33.941
uh...think bigger!

04:33.974 --> 04:36.076
Hmm. Unorthodox...

04:36.109 --> 04:37.244
and bold!

04:37.277 --> 04:38.312
I like it!

04:38.346 --> 04:40.314
In fact, I'm gonna give you
a promotion.

04:40.348 --> 04:42.916
"Director of Presentations."
How does that sound?

04:42.950 --> 04:44.318
-Okay.
-Fantastic!

04:44.352 --> 04:46.587
I want a presentation
by the end of the day.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.088
Uh, presen-ta-what?

04:48.121 --> 04:49.323
I expect big things
from you!

04:49.357 --> 04:50.591
[ Ding! ]

04:50.624 --> 04:53.761
But I don't even know
what this company does.

04:53.794 --> 04:56.229
**

05:05.373 --> 05:06.540
Aah!

05:06.574 --> 05:08.275
[ Laughing ]

05:08.308 --> 05:09.443
Shh!

05:09.477 --> 05:14.382
* Not looking both ways,
I don't care *

05:14.415 --> 05:15.983
* Just cross the street

05:16.016 --> 05:17.851
Hey, do you trust me?
Huh?

05:17.885 --> 05:19.453
Do you trust me?!

05:19.487 --> 05:20.454
Yeah, sure!

05:20.488 --> 05:21.889
Okay!
Here we go, then!

05:21.922 --> 05:27.027
Huh? Aaaahhhh!

05:27.060 --> 05:28.328
Ready?
Wait, what!?

05:28.362 --> 05:29.296
[ Buzzer ]
No!

05:29.329 --> 05:31.399
No, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

05:31.432 --> 05:34.301
* I hope that we can
take it slow *
Whoo!

05:34.334 --> 05:36.336
[ Mwah! ]

05:37.838 --> 05:38.706
Come on.

05:38.739 --> 05:39.907
W-where you going?

05:39.940 --> 05:42.242
Wait, wait.
I-I can't go up there.

05:42.275 --> 05:43.511
Chicken!

05:43.544 --> 05:45.846
Uh, okay, uh, fine.
Ugh.

05:45.879 --> 05:47.648
[ Groans ]

05:47.681 --> 05:49.983
Ah, come on, Panda!
On the double!

05:50.017 --> 05:52.520
Attaboy.
Come on, come on, come on!

05:52.553 --> 05:55.155
Ugh.
Why are we here?

05:55.188 --> 05:56.323
[ Sighs ]

05:56.356 --> 05:57.558
I'm so wet and cold

05:57.591 --> 05:58.926
and miserable
right now.

05:58.959 --> 06:01.228
Oh, stop it.
You sound like my whinny ex--

06:01.261 --> 06:03.531
Huh?
Panda, what are you...

06:03.564 --> 06:04.865
[ Gasps ]
Huh?

06:04.898 --> 06:06.166
Oh, my gosh,
oh, my gosh!

06:06.199 --> 06:08.836
Yes! I will marry you!

06:08.869 --> 06:09.870
Wait, no, I wasn't --

06:09.903 --> 06:11.004
I'm so happy!

06:11.038 --> 06:12.506
But I was just, uh --

06:12.540 --> 06:13.674
I love you.

06:13.707 --> 06:15.008
Y-you -- you love me?

06:15.042 --> 06:16.677
[ Gasps ]
We need to tell Daddy!

06:16.710 --> 06:17.778
D-Daddy?

06:17.811 --> 06:18.746
You mean your father?

06:18.779 --> 06:20.247
Yep! Ugh!

06:20.280 --> 06:22.182
I can't wait to see
his surprised face!

06:22.215 --> 06:23.584
Come on, let's go,
let's go!

06:23.617 --> 06:24.685
But -- But I...

06:24.718 --> 06:26.454
[ Groans ]

06:26.487 --> 06:28.689
**

06:28.722 --> 06:29.857
[ Techno music plays ]

06:29.890 --> 06:31.124
Man: Yes!
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

06:31.158 --> 06:32.626
Awesome.

06:32.660 --> 06:35.195
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, fabulous!

06:35.228 --> 06:38.466
Okay,
taking a quick break.

06:38.499 --> 06:40.968
Mm, that looks a bit too chubby.
Slim him down a bit?

06:41.001 --> 06:42.703
[ Keyboard clacking ]

06:42.736 --> 06:45.138
That doesn't look
like Ice Bear.
Oh, uh, hey there.

06:45.172 --> 06:47.407
You know, I-I wouldn't worry
about this stuff right now.

06:47.441 --> 06:49.443
Here, come on,
let's go get you ready.

06:51.612 --> 06:52.980
[ Scrape ]

06:53.013 --> 06:55.483
VoilÃ !
He is perfection!

06:55.516 --> 06:57.485
Ahem.

06:57.518 --> 06:59.753
Not yet he's not.

06:59.787 --> 07:01.221
We're gonna pull back
this tissue here,

07:01.254 --> 07:03.090
merge these layers to really
accentuate the fur grain,

07:03.123 --> 07:04.892
and we're just gonna
get rid of this altogether.

07:04.925 --> 07:06.393
And, done!
You're gonna be beautiful.

07:06.426 --> 07:07.394
Perfect.

07:07.427 --> 07:08.896
Ice Bear won't go
under the knife.

07:08.929 --> 07:11.064
What?! I was -- I was --
okay, okay, okay.

07:11.098 --> 07:13.901
Plan B -- I'm gonna need
a bucket of concealer...

07:13.934 --> 07:15.002
and a girdle.

07:15.035 --> 07:16.369
[ Gasping ]

07:17.505 --> 07:19.006
Oh, this isn't gonna work.

07:19.039 --> 07:21.008
Ohh, this isn't gonna work.

07:21.041 --> 07:22.442
I don't know what I'm doing.

07:22.476 --> 07:23.977
I don't even know what
this company is called!

07:24.011 --> 07:25.245
[ Groans ]

07:25.278 --> 07:29.116
Ugh, but everyone's
counting on me.

07:30.183 --> 07:31.752
Grr! Okay.
I've got five minutes.

07:31.785 --> 07:33.186
I don't know what I'm doing,

07:33.220 --> 07:34.855
but I am going to put
my whole heart into it!

07:34.888 --> 07:36.590
**

07:36.624 --> 07:39.092
[ Keyboard clacking ]

07:39.126 --> 07:41.428
Ladies and gentlemen,
members of the board,

07:41.461 --> 07:44.364
please welcome our new
Director of Presentations!

07:45.533 --> 07:47.968
All right. Thank you.
[ Clears throat ]

07:48.001 --> 07:50.303
Ants...atoms...

07:50.337 --> 07:52.606
a shrimp.
-[ Clicks teeth ]

07:52.640 --> 07:54.942
"What do these things
have in common," you ask?

07:54.975 --> 07:57.310
Small.

07:57.344 --> 07:58.445
[ Click! ]

07:58.478 --> 08:00.681
But what does
this smallness mean?

08:00.714 --> 08:02.115
It means no "Donut Fridays."

08:02.149 --> 08:04.451
No "Donut Fridays" means
unhappy employees,

08:04.484 --> 08:08.856
and worst of all, small
means...smaller profits.

08:08.889 --> 08:10.624
[ Overlapping talking ]

08:10.658 --> 08:13.460
Ladies and gentlemen,
there's no need to panic,

08:13.493 --> 08:15.963
for the reason I am here
is to give a solution.

08:15.996 --> 08:19.166
And that solution
is to think big!

08:19.199 --> 08:21.301
Monster trucks! Mount Rushmores!
Burritos!

08:21.334 --> 08:23.503
These are things our company
should strive for.

08:23.537 --> 08:24.972
It's that simple!

08:25.005 --> 08:27.207
Bigger ideas, bigger goals,
bigger fonts.

08:27.240 --> 08:30.978
The answer my friends...
is big, big, big!

08:31.011 --> 08:33.180
The end.

08:35.115 --> 08:36.516
[ Man coughs lightly ]

08:38.251 --> 08:39.219
I'm...

08:39.252 --> 08:41.254
Daddy,
I have wonderful news!

08:41.288 --> 08:43.390
Can we take a rest
for a minute, please?

08:43.423 --> 08:44.491
Samantha?!

08:44.524 --> 08:45.826
What's the meaning
of this intrusion?

08:45.859 --> 08:47.094
We're getting married,
Daddy!

08:47.127 --> 08:49.262
Married?
Hmm.

08:49.296 --> 08:51.599
So, tell me,
how did this happen, Samantha?

08:51.632 --> 08:52.833
Come on, tell him.

08:52.866 --> 08:54.768
Oh! Uhh, yeah, sir.

08:54.802 --> 08:57.337
We were on a bike.
We went through a car wash...

08:57.370 --> 08:59.873
And then he proposed to me
on top of the billboard!

08:59.907 --> 09:01.942
It was so romantic.

09:01.975 --> 09:03.577
Proposed on top
of a billboard?

09:03.611 --> 09:05.879
That's how I proposed
to your mother!

09:05.913 --> 09:08.281
I like your style!
Great men think alike.

09:08.315 --> 09:10.117
You have my permission
to wed my daughter!

09:10.150 --> 09:12.019
-[ Giggles ]
-Bro, you're engaged?

09:12.052 --> 09:13.453
And you!

09:13.486 --> 09:15.355
I didn't understand a thing
you said, but I love it!

09:15.388 --> 09:17.190
Let's do it!
-Wait, what, really?

09:17.224 --> 09:20.093
Yes. And I have just
the perfect new spokesman

09:20.127 --> 09:21.729
for our new venture!

09:21.762 --> 09:23.897
[ Doors creak ]

09:23.931 --> 09:26.366
[ Whoosh! ]

09:26.399 --> 09:27.968
What? We're selling
my little brother?

09:28.001 --> 09:30.303
No, no, no.
He's selling us.

09:30.337 --> 09:32.806
He's the new spokesman
for our chain of Boba shops.

09:32.840 --> 09:34.274
Bobarama!

09:34.307 --> 09:36.376
Your ideas, his style,

09:36.409 --> 09:37.978
and a perfect son-in-law
on my side!

09:38.011 --> 09:39.212
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

09:39.246 --> 09:41.048
We'll make millions!

09:41.081 --> 09:42.549
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:42.582 --> 09:45.085
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

09:45.919 --> 09:47.955
[ Laughs ]

09:47.988 --> 09:49.957
[ Cheering ]

09:49.990 --> 09:51.124
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
Money!

09:51.158 --> 09:52.626
Please save ice bear.

09:54.828 --> 09:56.630
Hmm.

09:56.664 --> 09:58.899
Notify the shareholders,
we're gonna triplify our stocks!

09:58.932 --> 10:00.433
And get me marketing
on the line.

10:00.467 --> 10:03.103
Hold up, everybody!
[ Sizzling ]

10:03.136 --> 10:04.672
Um, Grizz?

10:04.705 --> 10:05.906
Get down from there!

10:05.939 --> 10:07.607
I will no-- Whoop!

10:09.777 --> 10:10.644
Aah.

10:10.678 --> 10:11.611
Yeah!

10:11.645 --> 10:12.913
Whoo! Car wash!

10:12.946 --> 10:16.784
* Let me out
[ Groans ]

10:16.817 --> 10:19.486
* I'm free to run
Yeah! I'm with you, bro!

10:19.519 --> 10:21.922
* Rip these chains,
and it's done *

10:21.955 --> 10:24.024
Panda.
What is this?

10:24.057 --> 10:25.458
You're...n-naked.

10:25.492 --> 10:29.262
Sam, this is who I really am.
This is my true form.

10:29.296 --> 10:31.431
Uh, well, I think
we should take some time

10:31.464 --> 10:33.133
to think about
this marriage.

10:33.166 --> 10:34.802
Uh-huh.
We really should.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.036
[ Whooshing ]

10:36.069 --> 10:37.437
Freedom.

10:37.470 --> 10:39.339
I hate to say this,
but we bears

10:39.372 --> 10:41.341
are not suited
for this lifestyle.

10:41.374 --> 10:43.443
-Are you leaving the company?
-Yes.

10:43.476 --> 10:45.679
Consider this our resignation,
Mr. CEO.

10:45.713 --> 10:50.117
Onward, brothers --
to freedom!

10:50.150 --> 10:52.786
* Let me out

10:52.820 --> 10:54.187
* Free to run
Yeah? We're naked.

10:54.221 --> 10:55.455
You got a problem
with that?

10:55.488 --> 10:58.125
Mm! I'm proud
of my naked body!

10:58.158 --> 11:01.161
Freedom. Freedom.
* Let me out

11:01.194 --> 11:02.963
Grizz: Huh.
So glad we're not wearing

11:02.996 --> 11:04.031
those ridiculous clothes,
guys.

11:04.064 --> 11:05.298
Pan Pan:
Lesson well learned.

11:05.332 --> 11:06.800
Ice Bear:
Ice Bear wants a freedom Boba.

11:06.834 --> 11:08.568
-From Bobarama?
-Ugh. Let's try somewhere else.

11:08.601 --> 11:11.671
Shares in Bobarama actually
dropped 22% last quarter.

11:14.107 --> 11:16.744
**

11:32.793 --> 11:35.095
Grizzly: [ Sighs ]
Nothing.

11:35.128 --> 11:36.263
[ Slurps ]

11:36.296 --> 11:38.766
Save the crumbs, Panda.
We got to ration.

11:38.799 --> 11:40.333
[ Groans ]

11:40.367 --> 11:43.403
I'm starting to think
going to Japan was a bad idea.

11:43.436 --> 11:44.738
Don't give up,
Pan Pan!

11:44.772 --> 11:46.406
Just think about our new life
in Tokyo!

11:46.439 --> 11:49.109
Maybe we'll get a cool loft
on top of a sushi restaurant!

11:49.142 --> 11:52.712
Don't say sushi to me.
My stomach is eating itself.

11:52.746 --> 11:53.580
Ugh.

11:53.613 --> 11:54.714
Let me see the map.

11:54.748 --> 11:56.249
Hey, whoa!
I'm the navigator!

11:56.283 --> 11:57.317
No!

11:59.086 --> 12:01.154
-What?!
-What?!

12:02.923 --> 12:04.958
[ Both screaming ]

12:04.992 --> 12:07.127
[ Water splashes ]

12:11.331 --> 12:12.800
Ah! [ Gasping ]

12:12.833 --> 12:14.101
[ Coughs ]

12:14.134 --> 12:16.770
Guys!
Are you okay?

12:16.804 --> 12:17.938
Pan?

12:17.971 --> 12:19.206
[ Grunts ] Bro?

12:19.239 --> 12:21.741
[ Groans ]
Did we make it to Japan?

12:21.775 --> 12:22.943
I think so.

12:22.976 --> 12:25.445
A lot less buildings
than I imagined.

12:25.478 --> 12:27.981
[ Grunting ]

12:28.015 --> 12:30.050
Ugh.
Guys, slow down.

12:30.083 --> 12:32.652
Ooh.
What a pretty little --

12:32.685 --> 12:33.753
Huh?

12:33.787 --> 12:36.589
Aah!
Run, run, run, run!

12:36.623 --> 12:37.958
[ Hisses ]

12:37.991 --> 12:39.927
Aah!

12:39.960 --> 12:41.461
[ Hissing ]

12:41.494 --> 12:43.797
Aah! Oh, no!
We're trapped!

12:43.831 --> 12:45.498
[ Creature growls ]

12:45.532 --> 12:47.935
[ Roars ]

12:50.703 --> 12:53.173
[ Sighs ]
Thank you, universe.

12:53.206 --> 12:55.876
Uh, is anyone
else sinking?

12:57.477 --> 13:00.780
[ Both screaming ]

13:00.814 --> 13:02.515
I'm too cute to die!

13:02.549 --> 13:03.917
[ Screaming continues ]

13:03.951 --> 13:05.953
Dave: Grab the vine.
Hold on.

13:05.986 --> 13:07.220
Pull, pull!

13:09.356 --> 13:10.657
Oh, you poor things.

13:10.690 --> 13:12.525
Is anyone here
with you?

13:12.559 --> 13:13.861
Are any of you hurt?

13:13.894 --> 13:14.862
No, ma'am.

13:14.895 --> 13:16.663
Thank you
for saving us.

13:16.696 --> 13:18.198
I'm just glad
you guys are all right.

13:18.231 --> 13:19.867
My name is Karla,
and this is Dave.

13:19.900 --> 13:21.434
Is there a rescue team
on their way?

13:21.468 --> 13:23.636
No. Our box
just washed up here.

13:23.670 --> 13:25.638
We were trying
to get to Japan.

13:25.672 --> 13:27.374
Is this Japan,
by the way?

13:27.407 --> 13:28.341
Uh, no.

13:28.375 --> 13:29.877
[ Sighs ] Man.

13:31.378 --> 13:32.812
Hey, it'll be okay.

13:32.846 --> 13:35.148
We've been trying to find a way
off this island for a while.

13:35.182 --> 13:37.217
But someone will come
for us eventually.

13:37.250 --> 13:39.219
Then you guys
can make it to Japan.

13:39.252 --> 13:40.787
-You really think so?
-Yeah.

13:40.820 --> 13:43.823
Well, at least you're stranded
here with your husband.

13:43.857 --> 13:44.958
Oh. [ Laughs ]

13:44.992 --> 13:46.293
No, we're --
we're not together.

13:46.326 --> 13:48.728
Yeah, we sort of shipwrecked
here separately.

13:48.761 --> 13:50.497
Hey, we never caught
your names.

13:50.530 --> 13:51.698
Oh.
My name is Panda.

13:51.731 --> 13:53.233
And this is Grizz.
And that's --

13:53.266 --> 13:54.734
Hey,
what are you doing?

13:54.767 --> 13:56.136
Oh, this is
just my journal.

13:56.169 --> 13:57.570
-I was just taking some notes.
-Ooh, let me see.

13:57.604 --> 13:59.072
-Hey, wait!
-Oh, cool.

13:59.106 --> 14:01.308
You've been taking notes
on how to get off the island.

14:01.341 --> 14:03.576
Uh, yeah, I was a travel blogger
before we were stranded here.

14:03.610 --> 14:05.012
Hey.

14:05.045 --> 14:07.747
I have an idea.
Why don't you guys stay with us?

14:07.780 --> 14:10.383
Depends.
You have food?

14:10.417 --> 14:11.051
[ Laughter ]

14:11.084 --> 14:12.385
Grizzly: And then --

14:12.419 --> 14:14.087
And then this giant lizard
almost ate us,

14:14.121 --> 14:16.023
and Panda said,
"I'm too cute to die!"

14:16.056 --> 14:17.257
-No, I didn't.
-Uh-huh.

14:17.290 --> 14:19.426
[ Yawns ]
I think I'm gonna hit the hay.

14:19.459 --> 14:20.360
Don't stay up too late.

14:20.393 --> 14:22.062
-Good night.
-Night, Dave!

14:22.095 --> 14:24.164
So, are you guys
ready for bed, too?

14:24.197 --> 14:25.265
-Nope.
-Never!

14:25.298 --> 14:27.100
Come on.
You've had a long day.

14:27.134 --> 14:29.769
But we're not
[yawns] sleepy.

14:29.802 --> 14:31.238
Mm-hmm.

14:31.271 --> 14:34.541
Maybe if you sing us a song,
we'd be willing to sleep.

14:34.574 --> 14:35.675
[ Laughs ] Okay.

14:35.708 --> 14:37.277
But first,
get ready for bed.

14:37.310 --> 14:40.080
Okay.
Bed time stack is a go!

14:40.113 --> 14:42.782
-Ready.
-Ready.

14:42.815 --> 14:43.783
[ Laughs ]

14:43.816 --> 14:45.418
Hmm.
What to sing.

14:45.452 --> 14:47.354
How about a song
that I used to sing

14:47.387 --> 14:49.189
with my sister
when we were kids?

14:49.222 --> 14:51.258
But you have to go
to sleep after.

14:51.291 --> 14:51.959
Deal?

14:51.992 --> 14:53.360
-Deal.
-Deal.

14:53.393 --> 14:56.229
[ Laughs ] Okay.

14:56.263 --> 14:58.798
**

14:58.831 --> 15:06.573
* Lay down your head
in this warm and cozy bed *

15:06.606 --> 15:12.045
* And if I leave
before you wake *

15:12.079 --> 15:16.616
* Don't go thinkin'
that I have fled *

15:16.649 --> 15:22.322
* For these walls
cannot contain us *

15:22.355 --> 15:27.127
* We will go places
we've never been *

15:27.160 --> 15:30.497
* But know
that I'll be here *

15:30.530 --> 15:36.336
* When you return
to this home again *

15:38.871 --> 15:40.240
Karla?

15:40.273 --> 15:41.074
Yes?

15:41.108 --> 15:42.675
Do you miss your home?

15:42.709 --> 15:43.943
Of course I do.

15:43.977 --> 15:47.014
I miss my home
and my sister very much.

15:47.047 --> 15:49.782
But we're gonna find
a way off the island.

15:49.816 --> 15:50.783
Don't worry.

15:50.817 --> 15:52.952
Good night,
sweet bears.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.525
[ Grunting ]

15:58.558 --> 15:59.692
Aaah!
Dang it!

15:59.726 --> 16:01.094
What are you looking at?

16:01.128 --> 16:03.963
Coconuts are not easy to get,
you know?

16:08.801 --> 16:11.004
I usually
get a couple.

16:11.038 --> 16:14.207
[ Yawns ]

16:14.241 --> 16:16.143
Hey, Pan,
where's little bro?

16:16.176 --> 16:18.878
Ugh. Probably went out
for a jog or something.

16:18.911 --> 16:20.213
Yeah, probs.

16:20.247 --> 16:23.050
Good morning, sleepyheads.
Want some breakfast?

16:23.083 --> 16:25.385
I think
you're overdoing it!

16:25.418 --> 16:26.719
[ Thud ]

16:26.753 --> 16:28.721
Ow! Warn me!

16:31.424 --> 16:33.893
**

16:33.926 --> 16:35.795
All right, all right.
I'm coming.

16:35.828 --> 16:38.198
Hey, this guy is freaking out
about something.

16:38.231 --> 16:40.233
He was getting some coconuts
and then he went all crazy.

16:40.267 --> 16:41.334
What?

16:41.368 --> 16:43.703
We really need to teach him
how to talk.

16:46.273 --> 16:49.609
It's best to follow him
when he does this.

16:53.513 --> 16:56.083
Grizzly: Whoa! I wonder how long
this has been here.

16:56.116 --> 16:58.185
How have we never
found this before?

16:58.218 --> 16:59.986
Hey, go check out
the engine.

17:00.019 --> 17:02.089
Maybe you guys
shouldn't go in there.

17:02.122 --> 17:03.423
It might not be safe.

17:03.456 --> 17:04.724
It's fine.

17:04.757 --> 17:06.726
This thing looks like
it's been here for a while.

17:06.759 --> 17:07.927
Do you think
it's possible

17:07.960 --> 17:09.596
for us to get this thing
working again?

17:09.629 --> 17:10.730
Maybe. Hmm.

17:10.763 --> 17:13.066
Well, the technology's
a little dated.

17:13.100 --> 17:15.435
Any luck
with the engine, bro?

17:15.468 --> 17:16.436
Darn.

17:16.469 --> 17:17.537
Oh, hey.

17:17.570 --> 17:19.606
Maybe there's some
emergency supplies.

17:19.639 --> 17:21.241
Let's check the back.

17:22.742 --> 17:24.010
[ Groans ]
Nothing!

17:24.043 --> 17:25.612
Someone must have used it
a long time ago.

17:25.645 --> 17:27.514
Hey, guys.
I really think we should leave.

17:27.547 --> 17:30.183
This thing could blow up
or something.
We're done, anyways.

17:30.217 --> 17:32.885
Everything is gone.
Maybe our last chance.

17:32.919 --> 17:34.421
-Karla, I'm sorry --
-Don't.

17:34.454 --> 17:36.123
I just need to be
alone right now.

17:36.156 --> 17:37.190
Karla, wait!

17:37.224 --> 17:39.792
Poor Karla.
She's so sad.

17:39.826 --> 17:41.294
Hey,
why don't we collect

17:41.328 --> 17:43.296
some tasty niblets
from the forest

17:43.330 --> 17:45.365
and surprise her
with a little gift?

17:45.398 --> 17:47.100
Pan Pan,
you're a genius!

17:47.134 --> 17:48.235
Come on, guys!

17:48.268 --> 17:50.237
We're gonna give Karla
so much food,

17:50.270 --> 17:52.205
she'll explode
from happiness!

17:52.239 --> 17:53.740
Um, maybe not that much.

17:53.773 --> 17:55.142
Scrumptious.

17:55.175 --> 17:56.643
Delectable.

17:56.676 --> 17:58.145
Mm, maybe not.

17:58.178 --> 18:00.147
-Yeah! Whoo!
-Yeah! Whoo!

18:07.587 --> 18:09.656
Hey, what's the hold-up, man?

18:09.689 --> 18:10.390
Huh?

18:10.423 --> 18:13.660
Whoa.
What is this?

18:13.693 --> 18:14.661
Hmm.

18:14.694 --> 18:17.164
Emergency...

18:17.197 --> 18:18.765
su-please?

18:18.798 --> 18:19.999
Supplies!

18:20.032 --> 18:21.734
Open it, open it, open it!

18:21.768 --> 18:23.102
I've got it.
Whoa!

18:23.136 --> 18:24.437
Check out
all the stuff!

18:24.471 --> 18:25.805
Hey, what's that thing?

18:25.838 --> 18:27.340
Hmm.
It's an inflatable raft!

18:27.374 --> 18:28.641
Wait, so that means...

18:28.675 --> 18:30.810
[ Both ] We can get Karla
off the island!

18:30.843 --> 18:31.944
We got to go tell her!

18:31.978 --> 18:32.845
-Hmm?
-Hmm?

18:32.879 --> 18:34.013
Hey, what are --

18:34.046 --> 18:35.282
What are you guys
doing here?

18:35.315 --> 18:37.417
Ooh, ooh! Dave!
Check out what we found!

18:37.450 --> 18:40.086
With this stuff, we'll be
able to leave the island!

18:40.119 --> 18:41.188
Isn't that peachy?

18:41.221 --> 18:43.122
Dave,
is something wrong?

18:43.156 --> 18:44.123
-Aah!
-Aah!

18:44.157 --> 18:45.292
Hey! What gives?

18:45.325 --> 18:46.959
He's taking it all
for himself!

18:46.993 --> 18:47.960
After him!

18:47.994 --> 18:49.829
[ Panting ]

18:49.862 --> 18:50.830
What's going on, man?

18:50.863 --> 18:52.031
Look, bears, just --

18:52.064 --> 18:53.466
just forget
you ever saw this, okay?

18:53.500 --> 18:54.167
Give it!

18:54.201 --> 18:55.202
-No!
-Yes!

18:55.235 --> 18:57.036
No, you don't
understand!

18:57.069 --> 18:59.372
[ Screaming ]

18:59.406 --> 19:02.342
Whew!
Is everyone okay?

19:02.375 --> 19:04.377
Ah, come on!
Help! Help us!

19:04.411 --> 19:06.313
-Help us! Help us!
-Huh?

19:06.346 --> 19:08.381
I was planning on saving that
for when the time was right.

19:08.415 --> 19:09.782
Dave, I'm so confused.

19:09.816 --> 19:11.050
Why are you doing this?

19:11.083 --> 19:13.620
Don't you and Karla want
to escape and go back home?

19:13.653 --> 19:16.489
Karla can't know
there's a way off this island.

19:16.523 --> 19:18.991
It's the only way
I can win her heart.

19:19.025 --> 19:20.393
And soon, she'll see.

19:20.427 --> 19:23.330
She'll be as madly in love
with me as I am with her.

19:23.363 --> 19:26.165
And if that means
staying on this island forever,

19:26.199 --> 19:27.367
then so be it.

19:27.400 --> 19:28.901
So that's what
this is all about?

19:28.935 --> 19:31.838
What kind of love is this?
All lies and deceit?

19:31.871 --> 19:33.406
You're a-a weird creeper,

19:33.440 --> 19:37.410
and we're gonna get out of here
and tell Karla all about you.

19:37.444 --> 19:40.179
Oh, I don't think
you're going anywhere but down.

19:40.213 --> 19:41.381
[ Laughs ]
So long.

19:41.414 --> 19:43.182
And thanks
for all the fruit.

19:43.216 --> 19:46.353
You'll pay for this, Dave.
You'll pay.

19:48.621 --> 19:50.490
Looks like our goose
is cooked.

19:50.523 --> 19:52.158
Hang on a sec!
The raft!

19:52.191 --> 19:53.260
I'm going in!

19:53.293 --> 19:54.561
Grizz! No!

19:57.029 --> 19:58.398
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

20:00.467 --> 20:01.701
Pan Pan, we're free!

20:01.734 --> 20:03.836
Come on.
Let's go save Karla!

20:03.870 --> 20:05.572
[ Sighs ]

20:05.605 --> 20:07.274
Hey, Karla.
You okay?

20:07.307 --> 20:08.841
I brought you
some water.

20:08.875 --> 20:10.243
Oh. Thanks, Dave.

20:10.277 --> 20:13.012
I just worry sometimes that
we'll never get off this island.

20:13.045 --> 20:15.282
I'm starting to lose hope
a little, you know?

20:15.315 --> 20:17.884
Well, maybe
it's not the worst thing.

20:17.917 --> 20:21.120
I mean, we do have
enough food and shelter.

20:21.153 --> 20:23.423
And each other for company,
right, Karla!

20:23.456 --> 20:24.524
Ugh.

20:24.557 --> 20:26.393
What do you think
you're doing, Dave?

20:26.426 --> 20:28.295
Grizzly: Karla!
Get away from that guy!

20:28.328 --> 20:29.962
He's a creeper
of the highest degree!

20:29.996 --> 20:30.930
Ah! Ow!

20:30.963 --> 20:32.198
He's been lying to you!

20:32.231 --> 20:33.566
He's been keeping you
on the island

20:33.600 --> 20:35.034
because he wants you
to fall in love with him!

20:35.067 --> 20:36.436
In love?

20:36.469 --> 20:38.605
[ Chuckles ] What?
It's not what it seems, Karla.

20:38.638 --> 20:39.972
Haven't I been nothing
but helpful to us?

20:40.006 --> 20:41.308
Panda: Helpful?

20:41.341 --> 20:44.143
I think his journal
will beg to differ.

20:44.176 --> 20:47.447
Wow.
Would you look at that.

20:47.480 --> 20:49.482
[ Gasps ]
What is this, Dave?

20:49.516 --> 20:52.084
Okay, okay,
so what if I'm in love with you?

20:52.118 --> 20:54.253
Isn't it a wonderful thing
to be loved?

20:54.287 --> 20:55.888
We have everything
we'd ever want here.

20:55.922 --> 20:56.789
Hmph.

20:56.823 --> 20:58.825
Oh!
You messed everything up!

20:58.858 --> 20:59.726
Oof!

20:59.759 --> 21:01.428
No, you messed it up,
Dave.

21:01.461 --> 21:03.996
If it wasn't for you,
we could be home right now.

21:04.030 --> 21:06.333
Come on, Karla!
Let's get out of here!

21:06.366 --> 21:07.266
This way!

21:07.300 --> 21:08.968
No, don't leave me!

21:09.001 --> 21:09.969
Ow!

21:10.002 --> 21:11.838
[ Growls ]

21:11.871 --> 21:14.140
There!

21:14.173 --> 21:15.808
A raft!

21:15.842 --> 21:18.745
Oh, no you don't!

21:18.778 --> 21:20.313
[ All gasp ]

21:21.448 --> 21:23.950
Let that little
jellybean go, Dave!

21:23.983 --> 21:24.951
Never!

21:24.984 --> 21:26.185
Not until you promise

21:26.218 --> 21:27.987
to stay here with me
forever and ever!

21:28.020 --> 21:30.690
You'll be my queen, my muse,
a beacon of --

21:30.723 --> 21:33.259
Huh?

21:33.292 --> 21:34.694
Aah!

21:34.727 --> 21:37.597
No, Karla! Wait!
We were meant to be together!

21:37.630 --> 21:39.999
I'll do anything for you!

21:44.371 --> 21:47.807
**

22:06.926 --> 22:07.860
[ Yawns ]

22:07.894 --> 22:09.061
Where are we?

22:09.095 --> 22:10.162
[ Yawns ]

22:10.196 --> 22:12.732
Karla?
Karla, where are you?

22:12.765 --> 22:13.733
[ Gasps ]

22:13.766 --> 22:14.901
Panda, look!

22:14.934 --> 22:15.735
We made it!

22:15.768 --> 22:17.870
Oh,
isn't that peachy?

22:19.338 --> 22:22.675
**

22:31.250 --> 22:32.652
[ Laughter ]

22:32.685 --> 22:33.753
Whoa!
